{"id":1268028820,"question_id":3444,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1Â month","timestamp":1716691662,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"799 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1268028820/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find the Number of Good Pairs II","memory":"65.4 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public long numberOfPairs(int[] nums1, int[] nums2, int k) {\n        long res = 0;\n        int n = nums1.length;\n        int m = nums2.length;\n        \n        Map<Integer, Integer> freq = new HashMap<Integer, Integer>();\n        \n        for(int i=0;i<m;i++){\n            nums2[i]*=k;\n            if (!freq.containsKey(nums2[i])) {\n                freq.put(nums2[i], 1);\n            }\n            else {\n                freq.put(nums2[i], freq.get(nums2[i]) + 1);\n            }\n        }\n        \n \n        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n            for (int j = 1; j <= Math.sqrt(nums1[i]); j++) {\n                if (nums1[i] % j == 0) {\n                    if (nums1[i] == j*j) {\n                        res += freq.getOrDefault(j,0);\n                    }\n                    else {\n                        res += freq.getOrDefault(j,0) + freq.getOrDefault((nums1[i] / j), 0);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"find-the-number-of-good-pairs-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
